history.content: If we are able to find more than two qualified TAs to teach sections, we would  love to increase enrollment capacity to at least 90.  That is often difficult as by the time students have taken 188 and done well enough to consider becoming a TA many would rather spend their summer interning.    Absent that, as we get closer to the beginning of class it is likely that we might increase the size of each of the existing discussion sections by two.  Assuming you and the three students ahead of you aren't waitlisted for the same discussion section, you have a good chance. (Note 5 of the 6 students currently waitlisted for CS188 are waitlisted for DIS 102).

children.subject: Really hope the size could be expanded!

history.content: I tried to enroll in CS 188 over the summer and was put on the waitlist, and I'm #4 on the waitlist in a class size of 60. What are the chances that either the class gets expanded so that I am able to enroll or the chances that enough people drop so that I can get off of the waitlist? Any input/previous experiences enrolling would be useful. Thanks!
